Package: SoupX
Title: Single Cell mRNA Soup eXterminator
Version: 1.6.3
Author: Matthew Daniel Young
Maintainer: Matthew Daniel Young <my4@sanger.ac.uk>
Description: Quantify, profile and remove ambient mRNA contamination (the "soup") from droplet based single cell RNA-seq experiments. Implements the method described in Young et al. (2020) <doi:10.1093/gigascience/giaa151>. Provides automatic estimation of contamination fractions and corrected count matrices for downstream analysis.
URL: https://github.com/constantAmateur/SoupX
BugReports: https://github.com/constantAmateur/SoupX/issues
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), Seurat (>= 4.0.0), ggplot2 (>= 3.0.0), knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports: Matrix (>= 1.3.0), methods
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
LazyData: true
LazyDataCompression: xz
License: file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.0
NeedsCompilation: no 